  "ADAS framework is a generic and scalable software platform supporting energy-efficient deployment of AI algorithms on the multicore heterogeneous computation technologies. It supports all technology solutions, including localised and distributed computation settings as well as cloud offloading. It addresses resource allocation at runtime and hybrid coherent operation with optimised task allocation at design time.",
  "KIRMIK 1.0 SoC is a video SoC product manufactured with TSMC 65nm technology, which includes our in-house developed H.264 Codec Video IP and an open-source RISC-V 64-bit Linux-capable processor. KIRMIK, the first chip developed for video applications in Turkey, is equipped with Gbit Ethernet, SD-Card, UART interfaces.",
